{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72d2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6135"},"text":"§ 6135.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" W93 nuclear warhead acquisition process","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72d3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Reporting Requirements","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72d4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Upon receiving a concept definition study under phase 1 of the joint nuclear weapons life cycle for the W93 nuclear weapon, the Nuclear Weapons Council shall submit to the congressional defense committees a report that includes the following:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72d5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A description of the potential military characteristics of the weapon.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72d6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A description of the stockpile-to-target sequence requirements of the weapon.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72d7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" An initial assessment of the requirements a W93 nuclear weapon program is likely to generate for the nuclear security enterprise, including—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72d8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/C/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" adjustments to the size and composition of the workforce;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72d9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/C/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" additions to existing weapon design and production capabilities; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72da-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/C/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" additional facility recapitalization or new construction.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72db-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" A preliminary description of other significant requirements for a W93 nuclear weapon program, including—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72dc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/D/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" first production unit date;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72dd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/D/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" initial operational capability date;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72de-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/D/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" full operational capability date; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72df-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/1/D/iv"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iv"},"text":"(iv)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any unique safety and surety requirements that could increase design complexity or cost estimate uncertainty.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72e0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72e1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Not later than 15 days after the date on which the Nuclear Weapons Council approves phase 2 of the joint nuclear weapons life cycle for the W93 nuclear weapon, the Administrator shall provide to the congressional defense committees a briefing on a plan to implement a process of independent peer review or review by a board of experts, or both, with respect to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72e2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/2/A/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the nonnuclear components of the weapon;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72e3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/2/A/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" subsystem design; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72e4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/2/A/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" engineering aspects of the weapon.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72e5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Administrator shall ensure that the process required by subparagraph (A)—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72e6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/2/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" uses—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72e7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/2/B/i/I"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"I"},"text":"(I)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" all relevant capabilities of the Federal Government, the defense industrial base, and institutions of higher education; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72e8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/2/B/i/II"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"II"},"text":"(II)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" other capabilities that the Administrator determines necessary; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72e9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/a/2/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" informs the entire development life cycle of the W93 nuclear weapon.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72ea-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Certifications and Reports at Phase","children":[],"tail":" 3.—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 15 days after the date on which the Nuclear Weapons Council approves phase 3 of the joint nuclear weapons life cycle for the W93 nuclear weapon—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72eb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" the administrator shall provide to the congressional defense committees a briefing that includes certifications that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72ec-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" phases 1 through 5 of the joint nuclear weapons life cycle for the weapon will employ, at a minimum, the same best practices and will provide Congress with the same level of programmatic insight as exists under the phase 6.X process for life extension programs; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72ed-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the proposed design for the weapon can be carried out within estimated schedule and cost objectives; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72ee-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Commander of the United States Strategic Command shall submit to the congressional defense committees a report containing, or provide to such committees a briefing on, the requirements for weapon quantity and composition by type for the sub-surface ballistic nuclear (SSBN) force, including such requirements planned for the 15-year period following the date of the report or briefing, as the case may be, including any planned life extensions, retirements, or alterations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72ef-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Waivers","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Subsections (a) and (b) may be waived during a period of war declared by Congress after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72f0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s6135/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Joint Nuclear Weapons Life Cycle Defined","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In this section, the term “joint nuclear weapons life cycle” has the meaning given that term in section 6131.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaabf72f1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added and amended ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/dC/tXXXI/s3111/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, div. C, title XXXI, § 3111(a)","children":[],"tail":", (d)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/1370"},"text":"139 Stat. 1370","children":[],"tail":", 1462.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaabf72f2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaabf72f3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idaabf72f4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading